**`Repository::discover(".")` is CWD-dependent and fragile**: The server discovers the repo from the process's current working directory at startup. If the MCP server is launched from a different directory than intended (e.g., by an editor that sets CWD to the user's home directory), it will either fail or silently attach to the wrong repository. There is no way for the client to specify which repository to operate on, and no confirmation of which repo was discovered. The server should either accept a repo path argument, or surface the discovered repo path in `get_info()` so the client can verify it.